post_text: The peaches will be here tomorrow (8/28) around noon in Lamar. We apologize for the short notice - we were given short notice as well. We plan to be in Lamar from 1:00pm-3:00pm between the fairgrounds and the softball complex in the parking lot. Look for our yellow school bus. We will then be in McClave at the park from 4:00pm-6:00pm. If you ordered for multiple people, please plan to pay, take, and deliver those boxes. We will be actively posting on our school Facebook page today and tomorrow with updates. Additionally, to communicate with us about picking up your order, please text Kelly Curley (719-688-3343). In your text please include your name, number of boxes, and contact number. If you do not pay, pickup and/or make plans to pick up your peaches by tomorrow by 6:00pm, your peaches will be given to the next person in line on our waiting list. We do not have extra boxes at this time. If we do have extra, we will post later tomorrow. We do apologize for any inconvenience. Please SHARE this post to get the word out. Again, thank you all for your help and support for our kids.

post_text:
Today, and every day, we mourn the tragic loss of one of our Cardinals - Madison Stuart. Maddie lived a vibrant life and positively touched the lives of so many. Her family, friends, classmates, teachers, staff members, and community will never forget the wonderful memories we have with her and of her. Maddie was thoughtful, kind, compassionate, funny, smart - so many other things to other people. We will all miss who she was - truly a beautiful person.

If any individuals or groups feel the need to talk, there will be support available. The following will be available at McClave School this week. However, please feel free to contact the school anytime, 719-829-4517, and these individuals will get back to you.

Melissa Goble, School Counselor
Open office hours from 10:00am-11:00am, Tuesday-Thursday
Roni Vallejos, Hospice Grief Support Specialist
She will be at McClave School on Wednesday from 10:00-11:30am.
Brianne Howe, Principal
Open office hours from 8:00am-12:00pm, Monday-Thursday

We love you, Maddie, and will never forget you!

shared_text:
Colorado FBLA
April 12 at 4:37 PM ¬∑

For this week's Service Sunday... Our Colorado chapters just can't get enough community service! The McClave chapter teamed up with FFA to pickup trash around their town, delivered Meals on Wheels to over 30 families in the Lamar area, walked around their track in purple to raise money for March of Dimes, helped clean out their local food pantry in preparation for summer with NHS, and put on a free carnival for their elementary students. The Rock Canyon chapter has been raising funds to go towards Children's Oncology of America target pediatric AML fund to help a boy from a neighboring school with cancer by hosting give back nights and charity bike rides. Haxtun held three blood drives at their school throughout the year, wrote cards to military members over the holidays, and had freshman members deliver blankets to their nursing home. Keep up the great work Colorado FBLA! #servicesunday #helpingout #givingback #cofbla
